Geberit worldwide











We have sales teams in over 40 countries worldwide. Contact your local Geberit office.Choose your region


















The company GeberitThe globally operating Geberit Group is a European leader in the field of sanitary products. Geberit operates as an integrated group with a very strong local presence in most European countries, providing unique added value when it comes to sanitary technology and bathroom ceramics.













Sanitary products from Geberit – form and function of the highest calibre



































Home
Geberit worldwide
DE
EN














































Home
Products
Product range







Quality, comfort and design never go out of style.


Our sanitary products































The product area Sanitary Systems comprises all sanitary technology found in buildings (with the exception of pipelines) and is divided into four product lines: Installation Systems, Cisterns and Mechanisms, Faucets and Flushing Systems, Waste Fittings and Traps.The product area Piping Systems comprises all piping technology found in buildings for drinking water, heating, gas and other media and is divided into the product lines Building Drainage Systems and Supply Systems.The product area Sanitary Ceramics comprises all relevant sanitary equipment in the bathroom and is divided into the product lines Bathroom Ceramics and Ceramics Complementary Products.The market-specific product range can be found on the individual Geberit country pages
.





























































































Geberit product range


Installation Systems


Installation Systems
How today’s bathrooms are built









The installation systems from Geberit offer great design freedom and flexibility. They are used in renovation projects and new buildings. The wide range of products includes installation systems, installation elements, building blocks and concealed cisterns, and guarantees safe planning, calculation and implementation processes for both prewall and inwall installations.




Cisterns and Mechanisms


Cisterns and Mechanisms
The standard for modern flush technology









Geberit flushing systems are particularly noteworthy for their clean flushing out, economical water consumption, attractive design, customised functionalities and pleasantly quiet operation. This is especially true of the Geberit AquaClean shower toilets, which combine hygiene and comfort with elegant design.





Faucets and Flushing Systems


Faucets and Flushing Systems
Solutions for public spaces









Hygiene, functional reliability and highly economical use are the most important benchmarks for this product line. It includes electronic washbasin taps, pneumatic and electronic flushing systems for urinals and toilets and complete urinal solutions. The water-saving and energy-saving systems are available in different designs.




Waste Fittings and Traps


Waste Fittings and Traps
Clever connections that fit perfectly









Geberit offers maintenance-free, noise-insulated and functional drains and traps. These fittings allow for simple connection and operation of bathtubs and shower trays, kitchen sinks, urinals and bidets, as well as industrial and laboratory installations. The use of high-quality materials ensures safety for the entire service life of the connected sanitary appliance – even in concealed applications.




Building Drainage Systems


Building Drainage Systems
Technology with a systematic approach









Geberit has a complete range of plastic pipes and fittings for building drainage systems. This range includes normal, sound-optimised and highly sound-insulating piping systems for push-fit connections and welding joints, as well as the appropriate fire protection solutions. In addition, Geberit Pluvia offers a system that permits the efficient drainage of roofs with a large surface area.




Supply Systems


Supply Systems
Everything permanently sealed









Geberit supply systems made of metal, plastic or composite materials meet virtually every need, whether in household applications or the commercial and industrial sector. Geberit uses tried-and-tested pressing technology to connect pipes and fittings, while push-fit connections are also used for pipes with smaller diameters. 




Bathroom Ceramics


Bathroom Ceramics
Comfort, functionality and design variety









Geberit offers ceramic appliances for WCs, bidets, washbasins, urinals and shower trays through traditional, leading national brands. Many of these products have been developed in collaboration with internationally renowned designers and architects, such as Antonio Citterio, Bernd Brohammer, Michael Schmidt, Cornelia Thies and many others.




Ceramics Complementary Products


Ceramics Complementary Products
Contemporary, practical and versatile









Most of the ceramic appliance ranges are complemented by a wide range of matching bathroom furniture made of moisture-resistant material and boasting high-quality surfaces. Innovative shower cabins and partitions along with bathtubs and shower trays made of various materials round off the product range.



















Geberit product range








Click here to discover our product range interactively.























New products from Geberit – solutions without an expiry date



































Home
Geberit worldwide
DE
EN














































Home
Products
New products







New ideas spring from proven sources.


New Geberit products 2017











Geberit’s new or next-generation products must first meet an extensive list of requirements before they are released on the market. At the top of the list are quality and functionality, closely followed by design and ease of installation. Every Geberit product is backed by the knowledge and experience of numerous teams and accredited specialists from various disciplines.The market-specific product range can be found on the individual country pages. Geberit in your country




















Geberit AquaClean Tuma shower toiletThe shower toilet AquaClean Tuma impresses thanks to its elaborate product concept and simple, elegant design. It is available both as a WC complete solution with a rimless WC ceramic appliance and as a WC enhancement solution that can be combined with already installed ceramic appliances. The AquaClean Tuma offers a range of functions such as WhirlSpray shower technology, odour extraction, warm-air dryer and an ergonomically designed, heatable WC seat.













Roof drainage system Geberit PluviaThe well proven roof drainage system for large and very large roofs works according to the principle of negative pressure. It requires fewer outlets, pipes with smaller dimensions and fewer stacks than a conventional roof drainage system. The two most widely installed roof outlets in Europe with a discharge rate of 12 and 25 litres/second have been completely redesigned. They now have a more compact design and are easier to install. At the same time, the entire Pluvia range has been streamlined.













Shower surface SetaplanoThe Geberit Setaplano shower surface is designed for floor-even showers and is made of a high-quality solid surface material which has a smooth and warm feel and is non-slip even when wet. As many components are pre-assembled at the factory, among them the sealing foil, the time required for installation is reduced considerably. This shower surface is suitable for both new buildings and renovations.













Bathroom series AcantoThe Acanto bathroom series comprises everything that a modern bathroom has to offer nowadays: Washbasins in different sizes, rimless WC ceramic appliances, acrylic bathtubs as well as mirror cabinets, tall cabinets, washbasin cabinets and much more. The furniture elements are made from moisture-resistant materials and can be individually combined. They are highly functional and offer a lot of storage space.













Supply system Geberit VolexThe new Geberit Volex supply system combines two well established, proven and economic technologies: multilayer pipes and press connections. Volex offers a number of nifty improvements and is suitable for drinking water supply systems as well as radiator and underfloor heating systems. In addition to the multilayer pipes, Geberit also offers flexible single-layer pipes made from plastic.













Geberit tap systemElectronic washbasin taps for public sanitary facilities can be slim and elegant, yet still robust and safe to use. With the exception of the infrared sensor, all the electronic components as well as the mixer, valves and power supply are housed in a function box that is installed in the prewall in an easily accessible position underneath the washbasin. The modular tap system impresses thanks to its attractive price-performance ratio.
















































































































































































































