Products
Product range







Quality, comfort and design never go out of style.


Our sanitary products































The product area Sanitary Systems comprises all sanitary technology found in buildings (with the exception of pipelines) and is divided into four product lines: Installation Systems, Cisterns and Mechanisms, Faucets and Flushing Systems, Waste Fittings and Traps.The product area Piping Systems comprises all piping technology found in buildings for drinking water, heating, gas and other media and is divided into the product lines Building Drainage Systems and Supply Systems.The product area Sanitary Ceramics comprises all relevant sanitary equipment in the bathroom and is divided into the product lines Bathroom Ceramics and Ceramics Complementary Products.The market-specific product range can be found on the individual Geberit country pages
.





























































































Geberit product range


Installation Systems


Installation Systems
How today’s bathrooms are built









The installation systems from Geberit offer great design freedom and flexibility. They are used in renovation projects and new buildings. The wide range of products includes installation systems, installation elements, building blocks and concealed cisterns, and guarantees safe planning, calculation and implementation processes for both prewall and inwall installations.




Cisterns and Mechanisms


Cisterns and Mechanisms
The standard for modern flush technology









Geberit flushing systems are particularly noteworthy for their clean flushing out, economical water consumption, attractive design, customised functionalities and pleasantly quiet operation. This is especially true of the Geberit AquaClean shower toilets, which combine hygiene and comfort with elegant design.





Faucets and Flushing Systems


Faucets and Flushing Systems
Solutions for public spaces









Hygiene, functional reliability and highly economical use are the most important benchmarks for this product line. It includes electronic washbasin taps, pneumatic and electronic flushing systems for urinals and toilets and complete urinal solutions. The water-saving and energy-saving systems are available in different designs.




Waste Fittings and Traps


Waste Fittings and Traps
Clever connections that fit perfectly









Geberit offers maintenance-free, noise-insulated and functional drains and traps. These fittings allow for simple connection and operation of bathtubs and shower trays, kitchen sinks, urinals and bidets, as well as industrial and laboratory installations. The use of high-quality materials ensures safety for the entire service life of the connected sanitary appliance – even in concealed applications.




Building Drainage Systems


Building Drainage Systems
Technology with a systematic approach









Geberit has a complete range of plastic pipes and fittings for building drainage systems. This range includes normal, sound-optimised and highly sound-insulating piping systems for push-fit connections and welding joints, as well as the appropriate fire protection solutions. In addition, Geberit Pluvia offers a system that permits the efficient drainage of roofs with a large surface area.




Supply Systems


Supply Systems
Everything permanently sealed









Geberit supply systems made of metal, plastic or composite materials meet virtually every need, whether in household applications or the commercial and industrial sector. Geberit uses tried-and-tested pressing technology to connect pipes and fittings, while push-fit connections are also used for pipes with smaller diameters. 




Bathroom Ceramics


Bathroom Ceramics
Comfort, functionality and design variety









Geberit offers ceramic appliances for WCs, bidets, washbasins, urinals and shower trays through traditional, leading national brands. Many of these products have been developed in collaboration with internationally renowned designers and architects, such as Antonio Citterio, Bernd Brohammer, Michael Schmidt, Cornelia Thies and many others.




Ceramics Complementary Products


Ceramics Complementary Products
Contemporary, practical and versatile









Most of the ceramic appliance ranges are complemented by a wide range of matching bathroom furniture made of moisture-resistant material and boasting high-quality surfaces. Innovative shower cabins and partitions along with bathtubs and shower trays made of various materials round off the product range.



















